{"questionId":"14002","questionHtml":"<p>Describe the transformation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( {x + 1} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>correct name, correct magnitude <strong>and</strong> direction&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;name:</em> translation, (horizontal) shift (do not accept move)</p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;magnitude and direction</em>: 1 unit to the left,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 1} \\\\   0  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, horizontal by –1</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14002","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.S_4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Describe the transformation f ( x + 1 ) .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}